track_notes: A steady walk up along part of Alfred Wainwrights Coast to Coast / Cleveland Way National Trail. Expect to take around 45 - 60 minutes to reach the trig point depending on your fitness and pack size. Single route up only shown.
track_title: G/TW-001 Round Hill (Urra Moor) from Clay Bank CP

track_notes: A more interesting, imaginative but longer route than Clay Bank to TW-001. This one is from the Chop Gate (Yat) free car park. The full return route is shown as I took a slightly different way back. More info in my blog - see link from Summits Information page on the SOTA website. Two gamekeepers once approached me here whilst activating, they were very friendly, which made a nice change!
track_title: G/TW-001 Round Hill (Urra Moor) circular route from Chop Gate CP

track_notes: Double activation bit muddy in a few places, enjoyable route.
